cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.COM

This paper discusses the design challenges and solutions for New Radio-based access to Unlicensed spectrum (NR-U) with beam-based transmissions, which involves issues related to wireless networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), millimeter-wave communication (cs.MM), interference management (cs.CR), and communication and information theory (cs.COM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI, followed by cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, and cs.COM.
